value: Gui food vessel, bronze. Inscribed.  The bowl has a high foot rim, with two loop handles in the form of dragons' heads, with another animal below, possibly a goat.  The body is divided into four quarters, each with a t'ao t'ieh mask formed from butting dragon heads.  A frieze of hook snouted dragons above, and of grovelling dragons below.  With a cicada motif at the top rim
